index 0000000000..17c8392162
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/plane-ekf3-inertial-gps.md
@@ -0,0 +1,112 @@
+# ArduPlane experimental no-GPS waypoint navigation
+
+This Plane-only patch allows ArduPlane to execute a QGroundControl waypoint
+mission without GPS, ExternalNav, VisualOdom or MAVLink navigation
+measurements. It does not add firmware parameters.
+
+QGroundControl still uses MAVLink to upload the mission and receive telemetry.
+MAVLink is not used as a position, velocity, altitude or yaw measurement
+source.
+
+## Estimator configuration
+
+Use:
+
+```text
+Tools/autotest/default_params/plane-sitl-nsu-no-gps.parm
+```
+
+The configuration selects the built-in DCM backend:
+
+```text
+AHRS_EKF_TYPE 0
+EK2_ENABLE    0
+EK3_ENABLE    0
+AHRS_GPS_USE  0
+VISO_TYPE     0
+```
+
+GPS drivers and simulated GPS sensors are disabled:
+
+```text
+GPS1_TYPE        0
+GPS2_TYPE        0
+SIM_GPS_DISABLE  1
+SIM_GPS2_DISABLE 1
+SIM_GPS_TYPE     0
+SIM_GPS2_TYPE    0
+```
+
+DCM estimates horizontal motion from airspeed, attitude, compass yaw and wind.
+Barometer data provides the vertical reference used by Plane.
+
+## Initial geographic reference
+
+Latitude and longitude cannot be derived from inertial measurements alone.
+An initial Home is therefore mandatory.
+
+For SITL, pass Home once with `--home`:
+
+```sh
+./arduplane \
+  -w \
+  --defaults plane-sitl-nsu-no-gps.parm \
+  --model plane \
+  --home 55.7522,37.6156,180,0 \
+  --serial0 udpclient:127.0.0.1:14550
+```
+
+The SITL-only Plane code copies that initial reference into AHRS when no GPS
+instance exists. It does not inject subsequent position updates.
+
+On hardware, Home must be set through an existing ArduPilot mechanism before
+arming, for example once from the GCS. The patch does not invent or persist a
+geographic origin.
+
+## AUTO takeoff and waypoint mission
+
+Stock Plane requires a 3D GPS fix in `auto_takeoff_check()`. The patch accepts
+the DCM position only when all of these conditions are true:
+
+- the selected AHRS backend is DCM;
+- ArduPilot has zero GPS instances;
+- Home is set;
+- AHRS currently provides a location.
+
+Normal configurations with a GPS instance retain the original 3D-fix
+requirement. The launch speed check uses the standard DCM ground-speed
+estimate when GPS is absent.
+
+## Safety limitation
+
+This mode is intended for SITL and controlled research only. There is no
+absolute horizontal correction. Compass, airspeed, wind-estimation and IMU
+errors accumulate directly into the reported latitude/longitude, so long
+missions or real flights can diverge substantially from the QGC map.
+
+The parameter file keeps standard arming checks except GPS-related checks. It
+does not disable all pre-arm validation.
+
+## Expected messages and logs
+
+At startup:
+
+```text
+SITL home used for DCM dead-reckoning
+DCM: inertial position from Home
+```
+
+At AUTO launch:
+
+```text
+Triggered AUTO. Ground speed = ...
+```
+
+In QGC or DataFlash logs verify:
+
+- `GPS_RAW_INT.fix_type` remains `0`;
+- satellite count remains `0`;
+- `GLOBAL_POSITION_INT` starts at Home and changes only after arming;
+- `MISSION_CURRENT` advances through the uploaded mission;
+- throttle is released after the AUTO launch check;
+- no `VisOdom not healthy` message is present.
